  "prompt": "What question can I post on Quora to get credits?",
  "response": "To earn Quora credits, you need to post questions that are engaging, relevant, and likely to attract thoughtful answers. Here\u2019s how to create such questions:\n\n1. **Be Clear and Specific**:  \n   - Instead of asking \"What\u2019s the best phone?\", try \"What\u2019s the best Android phone under $500 for photography enthusiasts?\"\n\n2. **Spark Curiosity or Debate**:  \n   - Example: \"Why do people argue about pineapple on pizza? Is it actually a good combination?\"\n\n3. **Ask for Personal Experiences or Advice**:  \n   - Example: \"What\u2019s the most valuable lesson you\u2019ve learned from a failure in your career?\"\n\n4. **Tap into Current Trends or Pop Culture**:  \n   - Example: \"How do you think AI will change the way we work in the next 5 years?\"\n\n5. **Encourage Storytelling**:  \n   - Example: \"What\u2019s the most unforgettable travel experience you\u2019ve ever had?\"\n\n6. **Avoid Yes/No Questions**:  \n   - Instead of \"Is remote work better?\", ask \"What are the pros and cons of remote work compared to in-office work?\"\n\n7. **Add a Unique Twist**:  \n   - Example: \"If you could only eat one cuisine for the rest of your life, what would it be and why?\"\n\nBy posting high-quality questions, you increase the likelihood of attracting upvotes and engagement, which can earn you Quora credits. Remember to avoid spammy or overly broad questions, as they are less likely to generate meaningful interactions.",
